  "body": "[The documentation](https://github.com/ethereum/remix-ide) currently states:\r\n\r\n```\r\nInstall npm and node.js (see https://docs.npmjs.com/getting-started/installing-node), then do:\r\n\r\nRemix-ide has been published as an npm module:\r\n\r\nnpm install remix-ide -g\r\nremix-ide\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis leads folks to believe that the correct way to install `remix-ide` is via npm. According to https://github.com/ethereum/remix-ide/issues/2970, this is no longer the case.\r\n\r\nThe documentation should be updated to specify the correct (ie. non-deprecated) way to install remix-ide.",
